//! in recent Rust versions (1.82+). Because your procedural macro emits `#[no_mangle]`
//! while inheriting the macro invocation's span (`#[export_driver]`), the compiler attempts
//! to blame the invocation attribute. The compiler's suggestion to write `unsafe(#[export_driver])`
