                    // the easiest robust workaround is to append a space to the inserted string.
                    // The `-= 1` offset will place the cursor ON the phantom space, positioning 
                    // the cursor perfectly *after* the `.` and allowing the user to seamlessly 
                    // continue typing the column name (which will push that space to the right).
                    // Extra trailing whitespace does not affect SQL execution.
